{"parse":{"title":"Trial and sentencing of Robert H. Richards IV","pageid":46660289,"revid":834220826,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p><b>Robert H. Richards IV</b> is a convicted child rapist and great-grandson of chemical magnate <a href=\"/wiki/Ir%C3%A9n%C3%A9e_du_Pont\" title=\"Ir\u00e9n\u00e9e du Pont\">Ir\u00e9n\u00e9e du Pont</a> and heir to the <a href=\"/wiki/Du_Pont_family\" title=\"Du Pont family\">du Pont family</a> fortune.<sup id=\"cite_ref-DailyMail_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-DailyMail-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Conlon_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Conlon-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Biography\">Biography</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Trial_and_sentencing_of_Robert_H._Richards_IV&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Biography\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Richards, 48, is the son of Robert H. Richards III and Mariana, daughter of Mariana DuPont Stillman.<sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup> He lives in <a href=\"/wiki/Delaware\" title=\"Delaware\">Delaware</a>, and owns three homes, located in <a href=\"/wiki/Greenville,_Delaware\" title=\"Greenville, Delaware\">Greenville</a> and North Shores.<sup id=\"cite_ref-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup> He married Tracy Richards, but they later divorced.<sup id=\"cite_ref-CBSNews_5-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-CBSNews-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Rape_conviction_and_allegations\">Rape conviction and allegations</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Trial_and_sentencing_of_Robert_H._Richards_IV&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: Rape conviction and allegations\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>In 2009, he entered a guilty plea and was convicted of raping his 3-year-old daughter,<sup id=\"cite_ref-Conlon_2-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Conlon-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Barrish_6-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Barrish-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-BarrishA_7-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-BarrishA-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Ungar_8-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Ungar-8\">&#91;8&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Andrews_9-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Andrews-9\">&#91;9&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Alter_10-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Alter-10\">&#91;10&#93;</a></sup> after the girl reported the abuse to her grandmother.<sup id=\"cite_ref-CBSNews_5-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-CBSNews-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup> Instead of serving out his eight-year prison sentence, the sentencing order signed by <a href=\"/wiki/Delaware\" title=\"Delaware\">Delaware</a> Superior Court Judge Jan R. Jurden said that the \"defendant will not fare well\" in prison and thus the eight-year sentence was suspended.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Barrish_6-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Barrish-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Ungar_8-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Ungar-8\">&#91;8&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Alter_10-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Alter-10\">&#91;10&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-NZHerald_11-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-NZHerald-11\">&#91;11&#93;</a></sup> Delaware Public Defender Brendan J. O'Neill expressed surprise that Jurden would use such a rationale to avoid sending Richards to prison.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Barrish_6-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Barrish-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Ungar_8-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Ungar-8\">&#91;8&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>In 2010, allegations were made that Richards had also molested his son beginning in December 2005 and continuing for two years.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Conlon_2-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Conlon-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-BarrishA_7-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-BarrishA-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-CBSNews_5-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-CBSNews-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup> Police and prosecutors investigated but did not find sufficient evidence to pursue charges.<sup id=\"cite_ref-BarrishA_7-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-BarrishA-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup> Delaware Attorney General <a href=\"/wiki/Beau_Biden\" title=\"Beau Biden\">Beau Biden</a> later defended the sentencing of Richards to probation.<sup id=\"cite_ref-DailyMail_1-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-DailyMail-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-BarrishB_12-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-BarrishB-12\">&#91;12&#93;</a></sup> Although Richards was ordered by Jurden to go through in-patient treatment at a <a href=\"/wiki/Massachusetts\" title=\"Massachusetts\">Massachusetts</a> facility, he has failed to do so.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Fisher_13-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Fisher-13\">&#91;13&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-BarrishB_12-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-BarrishB-12\">&#91;12&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>In 2014, Richards' former wife, Tracy Richards, filed a lawsuit seeking damages for the abuse of his daughter.<sup id=\"cite_ref-DailyMail_1-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-DailyMail-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Conlon_2-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Conlon-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Barrish_6-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Barrish-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Andrews_9-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Andrews-9\">&#91;9&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Alter_10-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Alter-10\">&#91;10&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-NZHerald_11-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-NZHerald-11\">&#91;11&#93;</a></sup> The lawsuit also claims that the polygraph tests Richards took in April 2010 during his probation supported allegations that he had molested his son.<sup id=\"cite_ref-DailyMail_1-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-DailyMail-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Conlon_2-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Conlon-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-BarrishA_7-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-BarrishA-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-CBSNews_5-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-CBSNews-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Andrews_9-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Andrews-9\">&#91;9&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Alter_10-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Alter-10\">&#91;10&#93;</a></sup> These reports were provided to Jurden.<sup id=\"cite_ref-BarrishB_12-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-BarrishB-12\">&#91;12&#93;</a></sup> In April 2014, Superior Court Judge Richard F. Stokes denied Richards' request to seal the court files, stating that the proceedings were open to the public and this was a <a href=\"/wiki/First_Amendment\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"First Amendment\">First Amendment</a> issue.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Fisher_13-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Fisher-13\">&#91;13&#93;</a></sup> By the end of June 2014, it was reported that a sealed confidential settlement had been reached on the lawsuit.<sup id=\"cite_ref-BarrishC_14-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-BarrishC-14\">&#91;14&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p>The case has caused questions to be raised if the wealthy receive unfair preference in the legal system,<sup id=\"cite_ref-Ungar_8-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Ungar-8\">&#91;8&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Williams_15-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Williams-15\">&#91;15&#93;</a></sup> and compared to <a href=\"/wiki/Ethan_Couch\" title=\"Ethan Couch\">Ethan Couch</a>, whose \"<a href=\"/wiki/Affluenza\" title=\"Affluenza\">affluenza</a>\" defense famously earned him probation.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Williams_15-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-Williams-15\">&#91;15&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Trial_and_sentencing_of_Robert_H._Richards_IV&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist columns references-column-width\" style=\"-moz-column-width: 30em; -webkit-column-width: 30em; column-width: 30em; list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-DailyMail-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">^ <a href=\"#cite_ref-DailyMail_1-0\"><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-DailyMail_1-1\"><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-DailyMail_1-2\"><sup><i><b>c</b></i></sup></a> <a href=\"#cite_ref-DailyMail_1-3\"><sup><i><b>d</b></i></sup></a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation news\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.dailymail.co.uk/news/article-2597171/Beau-Biden-defends-judge-gave-du-Pont-heir-probation-admitting-sexually-assaulting-3-year-old-daughter.html\">\"Beau Biden DEFENDS the judge who only gave a du Pont heir probation after admitting to sexually assaulting his three-year-old daughter\"</a>. Daily Mail. 4 April 2014<span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">10 May</span> 2015</span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=a